Commerce Store Should Focus on Niche Marketing</h2>\n<p>Niche marketing is when an e-Commerce business focuses on a certain market subset. This can be distinguished by product features, quality, demographic, and/or price for a specific group.</p>\n<p>Catering to a niche market for a webstore is very important to business. In many cases it can mean the difference between success and failure.</p>\n<h2>Advantages of Niche Marketing</h2>\n<p>There are many great advantages to your shop having a niche product. Let&#8217;s take a moment to go over a few of these key advantages.<span id="more-49275"></span></p>\n<h3>Having a Niche Creates a Knowledge Advantage</h3>\n<p>If you have a shop targeted at a niche market, chances are high that you have a somewhat vast knowledge of this niche.</p>\n<p>A knowledge advantage is possible because as shop owner, you are generally going to pick a niche based on something that you are familiar with. If you aren&#8217;t familiar with the niche in the beginning then you should be by the time you open shop.</p>\n<p>Armed with your high knowledge level, you can create an authoritative blog about the product and/or demographic. An authoritative blog leads to higher site traffic volume, which generally translates into an increase in sales.</p>\n<p>Due to having a high level of knowledge of your niche, your business will be in a position to be very competitive in a constantly evolving global marketplace.</p>\n<h3>Lower Costs of Niche Marketing</h3>\n<p>A major advantage is that your resources will be better utilized because they are focused on marketing to just one market segment as opposed to multiple. Already having a knowledge of this niche gives you insight. Meaning that you will spend less time and resources trying to target them.</p>\n<h3>Easier to Market</h3>\n<p>As a result of having a niche product, it will be easier to tailor your message to your audience. You can be more direct and targeted in your approach. Without a niche you would have to be very broad in order to reach a widespread audience.</p>\n<p>Therefore, this could lead to more effective advertising due to putting all of your marketing capital to work on just one group. Otherwise, you would be spreading funds among several different demographics.</p>\n<h3>SEO Advantage of Niche Marketing</h3>\n<p><a href="https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/35291?hl=en"><strong>Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</strong> </a>is all about targeting keywords within your sites content to rank in search engines.</p>\n<p>When using a niche marketing approach, you target keywords that relate directly to your niche. A site that doesn&#8217;t have a niche would need to use keywords for several different types of categories and multiple different demographic subsets.</p>\n<p>Being able to successfully pull this off will allow your shop to rank much higher in search engines. This generally means that you will see more site traffic. Higher traffic should hopefully mean more sales.</p>\n<p>As I mentioned earlier, that knowledge could allow you to create an authoritative blog. Search engines love this type of content and it can very much boost your page ranking.</p>\n<h3>Customer Loyalty</h3>\n<p>Niche product e-Commerce shops make it easier to gain customer loyalty. Customer loyalty comes as a result of understanding your target audience. When you know what the demographic subset is then you can win their trust. Resonating with customers is a must. You can do this with company culture, directed products, and effective content. Consistent quality will also play a role.</p>\n<p>Once you can gain customer loyalty, you can focus less on getting new customers. In doing so, you can work more on existing customers&#8217; happiness.</p>\n<h2>Mastering Creates Barrier to Entry</h2>\n<p>Once you have become a master of all of the advantages of niche marketing, your business will have most likely become a major player in your niche. It should come as no surprise that this is an advantage unto itself.</p>\n<p>Your ability to successfully harness these advantages will create a steep barrier to entry into the niche market. If you master them then you can limit your direct competition. The more market share that you gain, the more of a barrier you create.</p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Niche marketing is an exciting way to leverage the potential of e-Commerce. Using this style of marketing has significant advantages because it allows you too focus on just one market segment. This means that you will have high niche knowledge, lower costs, and if your lucky creating an entry barrier.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/25/niche-marketing-key-e-commerce-success/">Niche Marketing is a Key to e-Commerce Success</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/25/niche-marketing-key-e-commerce-success/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:60:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Extension Updates (07/22/2016)";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/22/extension-updates/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0