essaging) is currently the most popular communication method available. Let&#8217;s face it! The vast majority of us are more likely to read a text message than open an email or even answer a phone call. Additionally, <a class="read-more" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/21/benefits-sms-e-commerce/">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/21/benefits-sms-e-commerce/">Benefits of SMS for E-Commerce</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Michael Stone";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13565:"<h2>The SMS Advantage</h2>\n<p><strong>SMS</strong> (aka. text messaging) is currently the most popular communication method available. Let&#8217;s face it! The vast majority of us are more likely to read a text message than open an email or even answer a phone call. Additionally, text messages just feel more personal. <span id="more-49127"></span></p>\n<h3>SMS Open Rate</h3>\n<p>According to research studies, the opening rate for text messages is 98%, versus emails 20% open rate (<a href="http://mobilemarketingwatch.com/sms-marketing-wallops-email-with-98-open-rate-and-only-1-spam-43866/">Mobile Marketing Watch</a>). Not to mention the fact that 90% of all text messages are opened within 3 minutes of being received (<a href="http://connectmogul.com/2013/03/texting-statistics/">Connect Mogul</a>).</p>\n<p>The fact that the open rate is so high compared to emails is a significant one. Instead of your emails stagnating (like we know we are all familiar with), they&#8217;re actually being opened and more than likely glanced at!</p>\n<h3>A Personal Touch</h3>\n<p>Text messaging can seem more personal to customers, especially with customer service. Compared to email, your customers will feel like they are talking directly to someone one-on-one and that they will be responded to more quickly as a result. This makes your customers feel important. We all know that a feeling of value goes a long way.</p>\n<h2>Uses for SMS in Business</h2>\n<p>There are a lot of possible uses for text messaging in business.</p>\n<p>Use SMS for marketing and sales by texting current promotions, product information, discounts, and even exclusive SMS coupons.</p>\n<p>Texting can even help with other important business activities — especially those involving customer support. Send order, shipping, and delivery information. Even use it to close sales and to receive customer feedback.</p>\n<p>The use cases are many and there are probably others that aren&#8217;t even mentioned here.</p>\n<h2>Examples</h2>\n<h3>Stock Notifications</h3>\n<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-49155 aligncenter" src="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-300x263.png" alt="Stock Notifications" width="300" height="263" srcset="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-300x263.png 300w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-36x32.png 36w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-60x53.png 60w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-219x192.png 219w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-325x285.png 325w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610-32x28.png 32w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/28610.png 400w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>\n<h3>Discounts and Coupons</h3>\n<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-49167" src="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-169x300.png" alt="SMS Coupon Example " width="250" height="444" srcset="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-169x300.png 169w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-768x1365.png 768w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-631x1122.png 631w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-600x1067.png 600w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-20x36.png 20w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-51x90.png 51w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-108x192.png 108w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-160x285.png 160w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642-18x32.png 18w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/IMG_1642.png 1242w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" /></p>\n<h3>Customer Support</h3>\n<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-49169 aligncenter" src="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-199x300.png" alt="SMS Customer Support Example " width="199" height="300" srcset="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-199x300.png 199w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-600x902.png 600w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-24x36.png 24w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-60x90.png 60w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-128x192.png 128w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-189x285.png 189w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash-21x32.png 21w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/desk_splash.png 629w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h2>Best Practices</h2>\n<p>With anything, there is a certain way to do things. Using SMS for your business is no different. Here are a few practices to employ to ensure effective use of this communication method.</p>\n<h3>Get Consent</h3>\n<p>In most countries, you must have explicit permission before texting your customers. It may be best to treat your SMS lists the same as you would your email lists. Require customers to opt-in and most importantly provide an option for them to opt-out.</p>\n<p>For example, in the United States, text messaging customers falls under the same rules as telephone calls and is regulated by the <strong><a href="https://www.fcc.gov/">Federal Communications Commission (FCC)</a></strong> via the <strong><a href="https://transition.fcc.gov/cgb/policy/TCPA-Rules.pdf">Telephone Consumer Protection Act</a></strong>. Under this act the only type of message allowed without prior consent are those regarding pending package deliveries.</p>\n<p>There are similar laws in the United Kingdom within the <a href="https://www.world-text.com/docs/legal.php"><strong>Privacy and Electronic Communications (EC Directive) Regulations of 2003</strong> and <strong>Data Protection Act of 1998</strong></a>.</p>\n<p>It would be wise to research the regulations of your country before implementing SMS into your businesses communications.</p>\n<h3>Frequency</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s important not to send too many messages to your customers. Too many and they will become less effective because they will become annoying to the recipient and they will more than likely opt-out.</p>\n<p>In determining the frequency, think about what would be appropriate if you were the customer. You wouldn&#8217;t want to be bombarded would you? In my opinion, between 2 to 4 messages per month is reasonable, though 4 may be excessive.</p>\n<p>Also, make your SMS subscribers aware of the amount of messages they will receive and how often to expect them when they opt-in.</p>\n<h3>Disclaimers</h3>\n<p>According to <strong><a href="http://www.ctia.org/">CTIA &#8211; The Wireless Association</a></strong>, your messages should include a disclaimer informing the recipient that <em>“Msg&amp;Data Rates May Apply”</em> to all text messages.</p>\n<p>Learn more about the best practices for text messaging for your shop by reading the <strong>CTIA &#8211; The Wireless Association</strong>&#8216;s <strong><a href="http://www.ctia.org/docs/default-source/default-document-library/industry-best-practices.pdf">U.S. Consumer Best Practices for Messaging</a></strong> publication (Note: <strong>CTIA</strong> is an international association).</p>\n<h3>Opt-out</h3>\n<p>It is important that you provide a method for customers to opt-out of receiving your messages. To do this, you can just allow subscribers to text &#8220;STOP&#8221; to your particular phone number.</p>\n<h3>Text Professionally</h3>\n<p>It is important that you be professional and use consideration when using SMS to communicate with your customers. Here are some tips.</p>\n<h4>When to Message</h4>\n<p>A good rule of thumb is to send messages only during common business hours. This would typically be between the hours of eight o&#8217;clock in the morning until five o&#8217;clock in the evening, Monday through Friday.</p>\n<p>Texting customers at any other times may be inconvenient to its&#8217; recipient and could result in negative consequences, such as a customer opting out of communications.</p>\n<h4>Use Proper Language</h4>\n<p>Just because you are communicating via text message doesn&#8217;t change the fact that this is a business communication. You need to be using clear and concise language. And most importantly, avoid using texting slang.</p>\n<h4>Text Value</h4>\n<p>Don&#8217;t waste your customers&#8217; time. Anytime that you communicate, you need to be adding to the conversation. Your recipients should anticipate something of value from your messages. If not, they have no incentive to continue to relieving them.</p>\n<p>The keys to texting professionally are to text only during business hours, use proper language without text slang, and make sure the messages contain value.</p>\n<h2>Popular SMS Service Providers</h2>\n<p>There are many providers for SMS messaging as a business.</p>\n<h3>Here are some providers:</h3>\n<h4><a href="https://bontact.com/">Bontact</a></h4>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-49171" src="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina.png" alt="Bontact Logo" width="338" height="70" srcset="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina.png 338w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina-300x62.png 300w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina-36x7.png 36w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina-60x12.png 60w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina-292x60.png 292w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo-retina-32x7.png 32w" sizes="(max-width: 338px) 100vw, 338px" /></p>\n<p><a href="https://bontact.com/"><strong>Bontact</strong></a> is a full-fledged customer support communication tool. It&#8217;s got multiple channels of communication: including live chat, text messaging, phone calls, or email. The best part is that you can access all customer interactions from one central dashboard.</p>\n<p>There we already plugins made for Wix, Shopify, WordPress, and several others for easy integrations..</p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.clockworksms.com/">Clockwork SMS </a></h3>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-49175" src="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo-300x80.png" alt="Clockwork Logo" width="300" height="80" srcset="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo-300x80.png 300w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo-36x10.png 36w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo-60x16.png 60w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo-292x78.png 292w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo-32x9.png 32w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/clockwork-logo.png 442w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.clockworksms.com/"><strong>Clockwork SMS</strong></a> provides <a href="https://www.clockworksms.com/pricing/">Pay As You Go SMS</a> and is compatible with many programming languages: including PHP, Ruby, Java, Python, and Node.js. This provider</p>\n<p>Plugins are available for WordPress, Shopify, and even Zendesk.</p>\n<h3><a href="http://www.slicktext.com/">SlickText</a></h3>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-49177" src="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-300x113.png" alt="Slick-Text logo" width="300" height="113" srcset="https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-300x113.png 300w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-768x288.png 768w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-631x237.png 631w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-600x225.png 600w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-36x14.png 36w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-60x23.png 60w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-292x110.png 292w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-635x238.png 635w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text-32x12.png 32w, https://www.jigoshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Slick-Text.png 800w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.slicktext.com/"><strong>SlickText</strong></a> is a feature rich solution. You can easily schedule messages and it even supports Auto-Replies These are great for letting customers know that you received their message. It makes mobile coupons simple to pull off. A huge feature is Facebook integration, which is possible with one click.</p>\n<h3>A quick Google search will bring up several other SMS contenders.</h3>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>SMS messaging is an underused tool in small businesses. It is proven to be a more effective communication method than email. SMS messages are opened more often than email and in a quicker rate of time.</p>\n<p>There are several uses, including marketing, sales, and even shipping and delivery.</p>\n<p>If SMS isn&#8217;t something that you have implemented in your business strategy then it should be!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/21/benefits-sms-e-commerce/">Benefits of SMS for E-Commerce</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/21/benefits-sms-e-commerce/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:60:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"SagePay Payment Gateways Updated";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/15/sagepay-payment-gateways-updated/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:82:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/2016/07/15/sagepay-payment-gateways-updated/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri,